<h3>What Stays the Same</h3>
<p>SEO fundamentals still matter for GEO. Technical health, <a href="/blog/on-page-seo-guide/">site structure</a>, mobile optimization, and page speed all affect whether AI crawlers can access and process your content. Content quality, freshness, and depth remain critical for both disciplines.</p>
<h3>What Changes</h3>
<p>The weight shifts from backlinks to brand mentions. <a href="/blog/what-is-topical-authority/">Topical authority</a> matters more than domain authority. Direct answers outperform keyword-optimized paragraphs. And <a href="/blog/schema-markup-seo-guide/">structured data</a> moves from "nice to have" to essential.</p>
<p>The biggest shift: in SEO, you optimize for clicks. In GEO, you optimize for quotes. Your content needs to contain specific, citable statements that an AI model can extract and attribute to you.</p>
